We need more monkeys!

459
00:28:11.500 --> 00:28:14.600
There aren't any more!
That's the whole barrel!

460
00:28:14.500 --> 00:28:17.700
Buzz. the monkeys
aren't working!

461
00:28:17.700 --> 00:28:21.700
We're formulating another plan!
Stay calm!

462
00:28:21.600 --> 00:28:23.800
Oh. where could he be?

463
00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:38.000
- Can I help pump the gas?
- Sure! I'll even let you drive.

464
00:28:37.900 --> 00:28:39.900
- Yeah?
- Yeah. when you're 16.

465
00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:42.100
- Yuk. yuk. yuk! Funny. Mom.

466
00:28:42.100 --> 00:28:46.500
Aw. great. How am I gonna convince
those guys it was an accident?

467
00:28:48.600 --> 00:28:51.600
Buzz!

468
00:28:51.600 --> 00:28:55.600
Buzz! Ha! You're alive!

469
00:28:55.500 --> 00:28:58.800
This is great!
Oh. I'm saved! I'm saved.

470
00:28:58.800 --> 00:29:01.700
Andy'll find you here;
he'll take us back to the room;

471
00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:06.300
and then you can tell everyone
that this was all just a big mistake.

472
00:29:06.200 --> 00:29:09.100
Huh? Right?
Buddy?

473
00:29:09.100 --> 00:29:12.500
I just want you to know that even
though you tried to terminate me.

474
00:29:12.500 --> 00:29:15.300
revenge is not an idea
we promote on my planet.

475
00:29:15.200 --> 00:29:19.100
- Oh. Well. that's good.
- But we're not on my planet. are we?

476
00:29:19.100 --> 00:29:21.100
- No.

477
00:29:26.400 --> 00:29:28.700
Okay. come on!

478
00:29:28.700 --> 00:29:31.200
You want a piece of me?

479
00:29:36.100 --> 00:29:38.900
- Owww!
- Buzz. Buzz.
Buzz Lightyear to the rescue.

480
00:29:38.800 --> 00:29:40.700
- Aah-ouch!
- Next stop.

481
00:29:40.800 --> 00:29:43.600
- Pizza Planet! Yeah!

482
00:29:43.600 --> 00:29:45.900
- Andy!

483
00:29:54.300 --> 00:29:57.600
Wh-- Doesn't he realize
that I'm not there?

484
00:29:57.500 --> 00:30:00.800
I'm lost!

485
00:30:00.800 --> 00:30:04.100
Oh. I'm a lost toy!

486
00:30:08.000 --> 00:30:10.400
Buzz Lightyear mission log.

487
00:30:10.400 --> 00:30:13.700
The local sheriff and I seem to be at
a huge refueling station of some sort.

488
00:30:13.700 --> 00:30:16.900
- You!

489
00:30:34.600 --> 00:30:37.200
- According to my nava-computer. the-
- Shut up!

490
00:30:37.100 --> 00:30:40.400
- Just shut up. you idiot!
- Sheriff. this is no time to panic.

491
00:30:40.400 --> 00:30:43.900
This is the perfect time to panic.
I'm lost. Andy is gone.

492
00:30:43.900 --> 00:30:46.200
They're gonna move from their house
in two days. and it's all your fault!

493
00:30:46.300 --> 00:30:49.400
My-- My fault? If you hadn't pushed me
out of the window in the first place--

494
00:30:49.300 --> 00:30:51.300
Oh. yeah?
Well. if you...

495
00:30:51.300 --> 00:30:55.500
hadn't shown up in your stupid
little cardboard spaceship
and taken away everything...

496
00:30:55.500 --> 00:30:57.600
- that was important to me-
- Don't talk to me about importance!

497
00:30:57.600 --> 00:31:00.200
Because of you the security
of this entire universe is in jeopardy!

498
00:31:00.200 --> 00:31:02.300
What? What are
you talkin' about?

499
00:31:02.300 --> 00:31:05.200
Right now. poised at
the edge of the galaxy. Emperor Zurg...

500
00:31:05.200 --> 00:31:07.400
has been secretly building
a weapon...

501
00:31:07.400 --> 00:31:09.800
with the destructive capacity
to annihilate an entire planet!

502
00:31:09.800 --> 00:31:13.900
I alone have information that reveals
this weapon's only weakness.

503
00:31:13.800 --> 00:31:16.200
And you. my friend.
are responsible...

504
00:31:16.200 --> 00:31:19.800
for delaying my rendezvous
with Star Command!

505
00:31:19.700 --> 00:31:22.900
You... are... a... toy!

506
00:31:22.900 --> 00:31:25.200
You aren't the real
Buzz Lightyear! You're a-

507
00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:29.900
You're an action figure!
You are a child's plaything!

508
00:31:29.800 --> 00:31:34.400
You are a sad. strange little man;
and you have my pity.

509
00:31:34.300 --> 00:31:38.500
- Farewell.
- Oh. yeah?
Well. good riddance. ya loony!

510
00:31:38.400 --> 00:31:41.700
- "Rendezvous with Star Command."

511
00:31:41.700 --> 00:31:44.100
- I Driver] Hey. gas dude!
- You talkin' to me?

512
00:31:44.100 --> 00:31:47.200
- Yeah. man. Can you help me?
- Pizza Planet? Andy!

513
00:31:47.200 --> 00:31:50.300
- Do you know where
Cutting Boulevard is?
- Oh. no!

514
00:31:50.200 --> 00:31:53.200
I can't show my face
in that room without Buzz.

515
00:31:53.300 --> 00:31:56.200
- Buzz! Buzz. come back!
- Go away!

516
00:31:56.200 --> 00:31:59.600
No! Buzz. you gotta
come back! I--

517
00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:03.300
- I found a spaceship!

518
00:32:04.400 --> 00:32:06.600
It's a spaceship. Buzz!

519
00:32:08.400 --> 00:32:12.000
Come on. man. hurry up! Urn. like.
the pizzas are getting cold here!

520
00:32:11.900 --> 00:32:15.300
Uh. Cutting Boulevard. huh?
- Yeah. yeah. Which way?

521
00:32:15.300 --> 00:32:18.300
Now. you're sure this space freighter
will return to its port of origin...

522
00:32:18.200 --> 00:32:20.500
- once it jettisons its food supply?
- Uh-huh.

523
00:32:20.500 --> 00:32:25.000
And when we get there. we'll be able
to find a way to transport you home.

524
00:32:24.900 --> 00:32:28.400
- Well. then. let's climb aboard.
- No. no. no. wait. Buzz! Buzz!

525
00:32:28.500 --> 00:32:31.300
- Let's get in the back.
No one will see us there.
- Negative.

526
00:32:31.300 --> 00:32:33.700
There are no restraining
harnesses in the cargo area.

527
00:32:33.700 --> 00:32:35.900
- We'll be much safer in the cockpit.
- Yeah. bu-

528
00:32:35.900 --> 00:32:39.700
- Buzz! Buzz!
That's two lefts and a right. huh?

529
00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:42.500
- Thanks for the directions. okay?
- Yeah. And remember. kid-

530
00:32:42.500 --> 00:32:45.200
- Buzz!

531
00:32:55.700 --> 00:32:58.700
It's safer in the cockpit
than the cargo bay. What an idiot.

532
00:33:22.300 --> 00:33:24.800
Next shuttle liftoff is scheduled for...

533
00:33:24.800 --> 00:33:28.100
- T-minus 30 seconds and counting.

534
00:33:30.900 --> 00:33:33.000
You are clear to enter.

535
00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:36.100
Welcome to Pizza Planet.

536
00:33:36.100 --> 00:33:38.400
The white zone is for immediate pizza-

537
00:33:38.400 --> 00:33:40.400
- Sheriff!

538
00:33:40.400 --> 00:33:43.500
There you are.

539
00:33:43.500 --> 00:33:46.300
Now. the entrance is heavily guarded.
We need a way to get inside.

540
00:33:46.300 --> 00:33:49.100
- Great idea. Woody.

541
00:33:49.100 --> 00:33:51.900
I like your thinkin'.

542
00:33:51.800 --> 00:33:54.200
You are clear to enter.

543
00:33:54.200 --> 00:33:56.800
- Welcome to Pizza Planet.
- Now!

544
00:33:56.800 --> 00:33:59.400
Quickly. Sheriff!
The air lock is closing.

545
00:33:59.400 --> 00:34:02.500
Jones. party
of five. your shuttle is now boarding-

546
00:34:02.500 --> 00:34:04.500
Hey. Mom. can we have some tokens?

547
00:34:04.500 --> 00:34:06.600
Ow! Watch
where you're going!

548
00:34:06.600 --> 00:34:08.500
Sorry.

549
00:34:13.400 --> 00:34:18.000
... nine. eight. seven. six.

550
00:34:17.900 --> 00:34:21.500
- five. four. three.

551
00:34:23.500 --> 00:34:27.000
What a spaceport!
Good work. Woody.

552
00:34:34.800 --> 00:34:37.800
Mom. can I play Black Hole?
Please. please. please?

553
00:34:37.800 --> 00:34:40.500
- Andy!
- Now. we need to find a ship
that's headed for Sector 12.

554
00:34:40.500 --> 00:34:42.600
Wait a minute.
No. no. no. Buzz! This way.

555
00:34:42.600 --> 00:34:46.100
- There's a special ship.
I just saw it.
- You mean it has hyperdrive?

556
00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:48.300
Hyperactive hyperdrive.

557
00:34:48.300 --> 00:34:51.500
- And Astro. uh. turf!

558
00:34:51.500 --> 00:34:54.300
- Where is it? I-I don't see the-
- Come on. That's it.

559
00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:56.300
Spaceship!

560
00:34:57.300 --> 00:35:00.500
All right. Buzz.
get ready. And-

561
00:35:00.500 --> 00:35:04.200
- And the universe explodes!
- Okay. Buzz. when I say go.
we're gonna jump in the basket.

562
00:35:04.100 --> 00:35:06.800
Buzz!

563
00:35:06.900 --> 00:35:08.800
- No!
Hey. Mom. if I eat all my pizza.

564
00:35:08.800 --> 00:35:12.500
- can I have some alien slime?
- This cannot be happening to me.

565
00:35:21.600 --> 00:35:24.400
- A stranger.
- From the outside.

566
00:35:24.400 --> 00:35:28.300
- Ooh!
- Greetings. I am Buzz Lightyear.

567
00:35:28.200 --> 00:35:31.300
- I come in peace.

568
00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:35.700
Before your
space journey. re-energize yourself...

569
00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:39.900
with a slice of pepperoni.
now boarding at counter three.

570
00:35:39.800 --> 00:35:42.200
This is an intergalactic emergency.

571
00:35:42.200 --> 00:35:44.700
I need to commandeer
your vessel to Sector 12.

572
00:35:44.700 --> 00:35:47.200
Who's in charge here?

573
00:35:47.200 --> 00:35:50.000
The claw!

574
00:35:52.200 --> 00:35:55.200
- The claw is our master.
- The claw chooses who
will go and who will stay.

575
00:35:55.200 --> 00:35:58.600
- This is ludicrous.
- Hey. bozo. you got a brain in there?

576
00:35:58.500 --> 00:36:01.900
- Take that!

577
00:36:01.900 --> 00:36:04.700
Oh. no! Sid!

578
00:36:04.700 --> 00:36:07.900
- Get down!

579
00:36:07.800 --> 00:36:10.700
- What's gotten into you? I wa-
- You are the one that decided
to climb into this--

580
00:36:10.700 --> 00:36:13.900
Shh! The claw. it moves.

581
00:36:18.000 --> 00:36:20.200
have been chosen!

582
00:36:20.200 --> 00:36:24.000
Farewell. my friends.
I go on to a better place.

583
00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:26.100
Gotcha!

584
00:36:27.900 --> 00:36:30.800
A Buzz Lightyear?
No way!

585
00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:48.000
- Yes!

586
00:36:48.000 --> 00:36:50.900
Buzz! No!

587
00:36:50.900 --> 00:36:53.300
- Hey!

588
00:36:53.300 --> 00:36:55.800
- He has been chosen!

589
00:36:55.800 --> 00:36:57.800
- He must go.
- Hey!

590
00:36:57.800 --> 00:37:01.600
- What are you doing? Stop it!
Stop it. you zealots!
- Do not fight the claw.

591
00:37:04.500 --> 00:37:07.400
All right!
Double prizes!

592
00:37:09.900 --> 00:37:12.400
Let's go home and... play.

593
00:37:25.900 --> 00:37:28.300
Sheriff. I can see
your dwelling from here.

594
00:37:28.300 --> 00:37:31.500
- You're almost home.
- Nirvana is coming.
The mystic portal awaits.

595
00:37:31.500 --> 00:37:34.100
Will you be quiet?
You guys don't get it. do you?

596
00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:37.600
Once we go into Sid's house.
we won't be coming out.

597
00:37:37.600 --> 00:37:40.100
- Whoa. Scud! Hey. boy!

598
00:37:40.100 --> 00:37:42.200
- Sit! Good boy.

599
00:37:42.200 --> 00:37:45.500
- Hey. I got something for you. boy.
- Freeze!

600
00:37:45.500 --> 00:37:48.600
- Ready. set. now!

601
00:37:50.700 --> 00:37:53.000
Hannah!
Hey. Hannah!

602
00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:55.300
- What?
- Did I get my package in the mail?

603
00:37:55.300 --> 00:37:57.700
- I don't know.
- What do you mean you don't know?

604
00:37:57.700 --> 00:37:59.900
- I don't know!

605
00:37:59.900 --> 00:38:02.800
- Oh. no. Hannah! Look. Janie!
- What? Hey!

606
00:38:02.800 --> 00:38:04.800
- She's sick!
- No. she's not!

607
00:38:04.800 --> 00:38:08.200
- I'll have to perform
one of my operations.
- No!

608
00:38:08.200 --> 00:38:11.300
- No. not Sid's room. Not there.
- Hey. give it back!

609
00:38:11.300 --> 00:38:14.000
Bid! Bid!

610
00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:17.700
- Oh. no. we have
a sick patient here. Nurse.

611
00:38:17.700 --> 00:38:21.300
- Prepare the O. R.. stat!

612
00:38:21.200 --> 00:38:23.500
Patient is... prepped.

613
00:38:24.900 --> 00:38:27.200
No one's ever attempted
a double bypass...

614
00:38:27.200 --> 00:38:29.500
brain transplant before.

615
00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:33.000
Now for the tricky part.
Pliers!

616
00:38:32.900 --> 00:38:35.500
I don't believe that man's
ever been to medical school.

617
00:38:35.500 --> 00:38:38.800
Doctor. you've done it!

618
00:38:40.800 --> 00:38:43.000
Hannah!

619
00:38:43.000 --> 00:38:45.900
- Janie's all better now.

620
00:38:49.100 --> 00:38:51.600
Whatever she says.
it's not true!

621
00:39:03.100 --> 00:39:05.900
We are gonna die.
I'm outta here!

622
00:39:09.800 --> 00:39:12.000
Locked.

623
00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:15.000
- There's gotta be
another way outta here.

624
00:39:25.100 --> 00:39:28.300
Uh. Buzz?
W-Was that you?

625
00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:39.600
Hey. hi there.
little fella.

626
00:39:39.600 --> 00:39:42.900
Come out here.
Do you know a way outta here?

627
00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:13.100
J-B-B-B-Bu- Buzz!

628
00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:14.200
B-B-B-B-Bu- Buzz!

629
00:40:23.700 --> 00:40:26.400
- They're cannibals.

630
00:40:28.200 --> 00:40:30.700
- Mayday. mayday.

631
00:40:30.700 --> 00:40:33.100
- Come in. Star Command.
Send reinforcements.

632
00:40:33.100 --> 00:40:35.700
Star Command. do you copy?

633
00:40:35.700 --> 00:40:38.200
- I've set my laser from stun to kill.

634
00:40:38.200 --> 00:40:42.300
Aw. great. Great. Yeah. and if anyone
attacks us. we can blink 'em to death.

635
00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:47.500
- Hey. you guys.
I think I found him!

636
00:40:47.500 --> 00:40:49.900
- Buzz. is that you?

637
00:40:49.900 --> 00:40:52.200
Whiskers. will you
get outta here!

638
00:40:52.200 --> 00:40:55.100
- You're interfering
with the search and rescue!

639
00:40:55.100 --> 00:40:57.800
Look. they're home.

640
00:41:02.200 --> 00:41:04.600
Mom. have you seen Woody?

641
00:41:04.600 --> 00:41:07.300
- Where was the last place
you left him?
- Right here in the van.

642
00:41:07.200 --> 00:41:10.500
Oh. I'm sure he's there.
You're just not looking hard enough.

643
00:41:10.500 --> 00:41:12.500
He's not here. Mom.
Woody's gone.

644
00:41:12.500 --> 00:41:14.900
Woody's gone?

645
00:41:14.900 --> 00:41:17.000
Yeah. boy.
the weasel ran away.

646
00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:19.300
Huh? Huh?
I told you he was guilty.

647
00:41:19.300 --> 00:41:23.400
Who would've thought he was capable
of such atrocities?

648
00:41:23.300 --> 00:41:27.100
Oh. Slink.
hope he's okay.

649
00:41:30.200 --> 00:41:35.000
Oh. a survivor.
Where's the rebel base? Talk!

650
00:41:37.100 --> 00:41:39.800
I can see
your will is strong.

651
00:41:40.800 --> 00:41:44.200
Well. we have ways
of making you talk.

652
00:41:53.500 --> 00:41:57.300
Where are your rebel friends now?

653
00:41:57.200 --> 00:41:59.700
Sid. your Pop Tarts are ready!

654
00:41:59.700 --> 00:42:02.100
All right!

655
00:42:12.500 --> 00:42:14.800
Are you all right?
I'm proud of you. Sheriff.

656
00:42:14.800 --> 00:42:17.500
A lesser man would've talked
under such torture.

657
00:42:17.500 --> 00:42:20.700
I sure hope
this isn't permanent.

658
00:42:20.700 --> 00:42:23.300
Still no word from Star Command.
We're not that far from the space port.

659
00:42:23.300 --> 00:42:26.200
The door. It's open!
We're free!

660
00:42:26.200 --> 00:42:30.400
- Woody. we don't know what's out there!
- I'll tell you wha-

661
00:42:30.400 --> 00:42:34.000
- They're gonna eat us. Buzz!
Do something quick!
- Shield your eyes.

662
00:42:37.100 --> 00:42:39.600
It's networking. I recharged it
before I left. l-lt should be good for--

663
00:42:39.600 --> 00:42:43.000
You idiot! You're a toy!
Use your karate chop action!

664
00:42:42.900 --> 00:42:46.600
- Get away! Hoo-cha!
- Hey! Hey! How're you
doin' that? Stop that.

665
00:42:46.600 --> 00:42:48.300
Back! Back.
you savages! Back!

666
00:42:48.300 --> 00:42:52.200
- Woody. stop it!
- Sorry. guys. but dinner's canceled!

667
00:42:52.200 --> 00:42:55.300
There's no place like home!
There's no place like home!

668
00:42:55.200 --> 00:42:58.800
- There's no place like home.

669
00:43:10.900 --> 00:43:13.400
Another stunt like that.
cowboy. you're gonna get us killed.

670
00:43:13.400 --> 00:43:16.200
- Don't tell me what to do.
- Shh!

671
00:43:33.800 --> 00:43:36.900
Yee-haw! Giddyap. pardner!

672
00:43:36.900 --> 00:43:41.000
- We got to get this wagon
train a-movin'!

673
00:43:42.600 --> 00:43:45.000
- Split up!

674
00:43:50.400 --> 00:43:53.200
Hmm?

675
00:44:04.900 --> 00:44:07.700
Calling Buzz Lightyear.
Come in. Buzz Lightyear.

676
00:44:07.700 --> 00:44:11.300
- This is Star Command.
Buzz Lightyear. do you read me?
- Star Command!

677
00:44:11.300 --> 00:44:13.800
Buzz Lightyear responding.
Read you loud and clear.

678
00:44:13.900 --> 00:44:16.100
Buzz Lightyear.
planet Earth needs your help.

679
00:44:16.100 --> 00:44:18.400
- On the way!
- Buzz Lightyear!

680
00:44:18.400 --> 00:44:22.500
The world's greatest superhero!
Now the world's greatest toy!

681
00:44:22.400 --> 00:44:25.200
Buzz has it all!
Locking wrist communicator!

682
00:44:25.200 --> 00:44:27.900
- Calling Buzz Lightyear!
- Karate chop action!

683
00:44:27.900 --> 00:44:30.500
- Wow!
- Pulsating laser light!

684
00:44:30.500 --> 00:44:33.000
- Total annihilation!
- Multi-phase voice simulator!

685
00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:35.100
There's a secret
mission in uncharted space.

686
00:44:35.100 --> 00:44:36.700
There's
a secret mission in uncharted space.

687
00:44:37.900 --> 00:44:40.500
And best of all.
high pressure space wings!

688
00:44:40.500 --> 00:44:43.600
- To infinity and beyond!
- Not a flying toy.

689
00:44:43.600 --> 00:44:45.000
Get your Buzz Lightyear action figure...

690
00:44:46.200 --> 00:44:48.700
- and save a galaxy near you!
- Buzz Lightyear!

691
00:44:48.700 --> 00:44:52.400
Available at all Al's Toy Barn outlets
in the Tri-county area.

692
00:44:52.300 --> 00:44:53.800
And welcome back...

693
00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:56.500
to the Point Richmond
Bowling Championship.

694
00:44:59.100 --> 00:45:03.300
# Out among the stars I sit #

695
00:45:03.400 --> 00:45:06.000
# Way beyond the moon #

696
00:45:07.300 --> 00:45:11.800
# In my silver ship I sailed #

697
00:45:11.700 --> 00:45:15.800
# To a dream
that ended too soon #

698
00:45:15.700 --> 00:45:18.500
# Now I know exactly #

699
00:45:18.500 --> 00:45:21.900
-# Who I am and what I'm here for #

700
00:45:21.900 --> 00:45:25.300
You are a toy! You can't fly!

701
00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:31.400
# And I will go sailing #

702
00:45:32.500 --> 00:45:35.000
# No more #

703
00:45:39.200 --> 00:45:43.400
# But no. it can't be true #

704
00:45:43.300 --> 00:45:46.300
# I could fly if I wanted to #

705
00:45:46.300 --> 00:45:48.800
# Like a bird in the sky #

706
00:45:48.800 --> 00:45:51.800
# If I believed I could fly #

707
00:45:51.800 --> 00:45:54.900
# Why. I'd fly #

708
00:45:54.900 --> 00:45:57.600
To infinity and beyond!

709
00:46:12.600 --> 00:46:16.300
# - Clearly. I. #

710
00:46:16.200 --> 00:46:21.000
# Will go sailing #

711
00:46:37.100 --> 00:46:39.300
- Mom! Mom. have you seen
my Sally doll?

712
00:46:39.400 --> 00:46:41.600
What. dear? What was that?

713
00:46:42.500 --> 00:46:45.000
Never mind!

714
00:46:49.100 --> 00:46:51.500
Oof! Oof!

715
00:46:51.500 --> 00:46:54.400
Buzz. the coast is clear.
Buzz. where are you?

716
00:46:54.400 --> 00:46:57.900
There's a secret
mission. in uncharted space. Let's go.

717
00:46:57.900 --> 00:47:01.800
Really? That is so interesting.

718
00:47:01.700 --> 00:47:05.100
Would you like some tea.
Mrs. Nesbitt?

719
00:47:05.100 --> 00:47:08.800
- Buzz!
- It's so nice you could join us
on such late notice.

720
00:47:08.700 --> 00:47:12.600
- Oh. no!
- What a lovely hat. Mrs. Nesbitt.

721
00:47:12.600 --> 00:47:14.800
It goes quite well
with your head

722
00:47:14.800 --> 00:47:17.900
Hannah! Oh. Hannah!

723
00:47:17.900 --> 00:47:20.700
Mom? Please excuse me. ladies.

724
00:47:20.700 --> 00:47:23.000
I'll be right back.

725
00:47:25.300 --> 00:47:28.800
What is it. Mom?
Mom. where are you?

726
00:47:28.700 --> 00:47:31.500
Buzz. Hey.
Buzz. are you okay?

727
00:47:31.500 --> 00:47:34.600
Gone!
It's all gone.

728
00:47:34.600 --> 00:47:37.500
All of it's gone.
Bye-bye. Whoo-whoo. See ya.

729
00:47:37.500 --> 00:47:41.200
- What happened to you?
- One minute you're defending
the whole galaxy.

730
00:47:41.200 --> 00:47:45.600
And suddenly you find
yourself suckin' down Darjeeling with...

731
00:47:45.500 --> 00:47:48.000
Marie Antoinette
and her little sister.

732
00:47:49.900 --> 00:47:52.200
I think you've had
enough tea for today.

733
00:47:52.200 --> 00:47:54.100
Let's get you
outta here. Buzz.

734
00:47:54.200 --> 00:47:57.100
Don't you get it?
You see the hat?

735
00:47:57.000 --> 00:48:01.600
- I am Mrs. Nesbitt! Ha-ha-ha-ha!
- Snap out of it. Buzz!

736
00:48:04.200 --> 00:48:07.500
- I-l-I'm sorry. I-
You're right.

737
00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:09.400
I am just a little depressed.
That's all.

738
00:48:09.400 --> 00:48:12.000
--I can get through this.

739
00:48:12.000 --> 00:48:13.900
- Oh. I'm a sham!
- Shh!

740
00:48:13.900 --> 00:48:15.600
- Look at me.
- Quiet. Buzz.

741
00:48:15.600 --> 00:48:18.000
I can't even
fly out of a window.

742
00:48:18.000 --> 00:48:22.400
The hat look good?
Tell me the hat look good.

743
00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:26.500
- The apron is a bit much.
-"Out the window"!
Buzz. you're a genius!

744
00:48:26.400 --> 00:48:28.400
- Come on. come on. This way.

745
00:48:28.400 --> 00:48:31.400
Years of academy.
training. wasted!

746
00:48:31.400 --> 00:48:33.300
Ha. ha. B-3.

747
00:48:33.300 --> 00:48:35.200
- Miss! G-6.
- Oh!

748
00:48:35.200 --> 00:48:37.600
- You sunk it. Are you peeking?
- Heh. heh!

749
00:48:37.600 --> 00:48:40.900
Oh. quit your whinin' and pay up.
No. no. not the ear.

750
00:48:40.900 --> 00:48:43.300
- Give me the nose. Come on.
- How about three out of five?

751
00:48:43.300 --> 00:48:48.300
Hey. guys! Guys! Hey!

752
00:48:48.200 --> 00:48:50.500
- Son of a building block. It's Woody.
- He's in the psycho's bedroom.

753
00:48:50.500 --> 00:48:53.600
- Ha. ha! Hi!
- Everyone! It's Woody!

754
00:48:53.500 --> 00:48:55.200
- Woody?
- You're kidding!
- Woody?

755
00:48:55.200 --> 00:48:57.600
Ha! We're gonna
get outta here. Buzz.

756
00:48:57.600 --> 00:48:59.500
Buzz?

757
00:49:04.100 --> 00:49:05.900
- Hey. look!
- Woody!

758
00:49:05.900 --> 00:49:07.700
Oh. boy. am I glad
to see you guys.

759
00:49:07.700 --> 00:49:10.300
- I knew you'd come back. Woody.
- What are you doin' over there?

760
00:49:10.300 --> 00:49:12.600
It's a long story. Bo.
I'll explain later.

761
00:49:12.600 --> 00:49:14.500
Here! Catch this!

762
00:49:14.500 --> 00:49:15.600
Ha!

763
00:49:15.700 --> 00:49:18.100
- Whoa! I've got it. Woody.
- He got it. Woody.

764
00:49:18.100 --> 00:49:21.000
Good goin'. Slick. Now just.
just tie it on to somethin'.

765
00:49:21.000 --> 00:49:23.900
- Wait. wait. wait. wait. I got
a better idea. How 'bout we don't?
- Hey!

766
00:49:23.800 --> 00:49:26.600
- Potato Head.
- Did you all take
stupid pills this morning?

767
00:49:26.600 --> 00:49:28.500
Have you forgotten
what he did to Buzz?

768
00:49:28.500 --> 00:49:30.400
And now you wanna let him
back over here?

769
00:49:30.400 --> 00:49:34.700
No! No. no. no. no. no! You got it-
You got it all wrong. Potato Head.

770
00:49:34.700 --> 00:49:36.900
Buzz is fine. Buzz is right here.
He's with me!

771
00:49:36.900 --> 00:49:40.200
- You are a liar!
- No. I'm not. Buzz. come over here.

772
00:49:40.100 --> 00:49:44.700
Tell the nice boys that you're-
that you're not dead.

773
00:49:44.600 --> 00:49:47.600
Just a sec!

774
00:49:47.600 --> 00:49:51.600
Buzz. will you get up here
and give me a hand?

775
00:49:51.600 --> 00:49:54.300
That's very funny. Buzz.

776
00:49:54.300 --> 00:49:56.800
- This is serious!
- Hey. Woody! Where'd ya go?

777
00:49:56.800 --> 00:49:58.700
He's lying. Buzz ain't there.

778
00:49:58.700 --> 00:50:02.000
Oh! Hi. Buzz!

779
00:50:02.000 --> 00:50:05.100
Why don't you say hello
to the guys over there?

780
00:50:05.100 --> 00:50:08.400
Hiya. fellas! To infinity and beyond!

781
00:50:08.300 --> 00:50:10.000
Hey. look!
It's Buzz!

782
00:50:10.100 --> 00:50:14.600
Hey. Buzz. let's show the guys
our new secret best friends handshake.

783
00:50:14.500 --> 00:50:16.400
Give me five. man!

784
00:50:16.400 --> 00:50:18.200
Something's screwy here.

785
00:50:18.200 --> 00:50:20.700
So you see we're friends now. guys.
Aren't we. Buzz?

786
00:50:20.700 --> 00:50:22.600
You bet. Give me a hug.

787
00:50:22.600 --> 00:50:24.900
Ho-ho! Boy. I love you too.

788
00:50:24.900 --> 00:50:26.800
See? It is Buzz.

789
00:50:26.800 --> 00:50:29.400
- Now give back the lights. Potato Head.
- Wait just a minute.

790
00:50:29.400 --> 00:50:32.800
- What are you tryin' to pull?
- Nothing!

791
00:50:36.100 --> 00:50:38.000
- Oh. that is disgusting.
- Murderer!

792
00:50:38.100 --> 00:50:40.300
- No! No. no. no. no. no!
- You murdering dog!

793
00:50:40.300 --> 00:50:42.800
- It's not what you think. I swear!
- Save it for the jury.

794
00:50:42.800 --> 00:50:44.800
I hope Sid pulls
your voice box out. ya creep.

795
00:50:44.800 --> 00:50:47.200
No. no! No. no!
Don't leave! Don't leave!

796
00:50:47.200 --> 00:50:49.600
Ya gotta help us. please! You don't
know what it's like over here!

797
00:50:49.600 --> 00:50:51.500
Come on.
Let's get outta here.

798
00:50:51.500 --> 00:50:54.000
Go back to your lives. citizens.
Show's over.

799
00:50:54.000 --> 00:50:56.000
Come back! Slink!

800
00:50:56.100 --> 00:51:00.400
Slink! Please!
Please! Listen to me!

801
00:51:00.300 --> 00:51:03.300
No! No! Come back!

802
00:51:03.300 --> 00:51:06.100
Slinky!

803
00:51:14.000 --> 00:51:16.700
Buzz! Go away!

804
00:51:16.700 --> 00:51:19.700
You disgusting freaks!
Aaah!

805
00:51:19.700 --> 00:51:23.400
All right. back!
Back. you cannibals! Aah! Oof!

806
00:51:26.200 --> 00:51:30.100
He is still alive. and you're
not gonna get him. you monsters!

807
00:51:30.100 --> 00:51:32.000
What are you doin'?

808
00:51:34.300 --> 00:51:36.500
Hey. Hey. they fixed you.

809
00:51:39.500 --> 00:51:41.500
But-- But they're cannibals.

810
00:51:41.500 --> 00:51:45.300
We saw them eat
those other toys.

811
00:51:51.700 --> 00:51:54.300
Uh. sorry. l-l-l thought
that you were gonna--

812
00:51:54.300 --> 00:51:56.800
You know. you know. eat my friend.

813
00:51:56.800 --> 00:51:58.800
Hey. no. no. wait. hey!

814
00:51:58.800 --> 00:52:00.600
- What's wrong?
- Sid?

815
00:52:00.600 --> 00:52:01.900
Not now. Mom! I'm busy!

816
00:52:02.000 --> 00:52:04.900
- Sid! Buzz. come on!
- You left that door open.

817
00:52:04.900 --> 00:52:09.800
Get up! Use your legs! Fine!
Let Sid trash you. but don't blame me!

818
00:52:10.600 --> 00:52:13.800
It came!
It finally came!

819
00:52:13.800 --> 00:52:17.000
Ha. ha!

820
00:52:16.900 --> 00:52:18.800
"The Big One."

821
00:52:21.700 --> 00:52:23.700
"Extremely dangerous.

822
00:52:23.700 --> 00:52:26.400
Keep out of reach of children."

823
00:52:27.900 --> 00:52:31.400
Cool!
What am I gonna blow?

824
00:52:31.300 --> 00:52:34.200
Man. Hey. where's
that wimpy cowboy doll?

825
00:52:47.400 --> 00:52:52.300
Yes. I've always wanted
to put a spaceman into orbit.

826
00:52:58.800 --> 00:53:00.600
- Heh. heh.

827
00:53:00.700 --> 00:53:04.500
Now. Yes.

828
00:53:07.400 --> 00:53:10.500
- Oh. no!

829
00:53:12.600 --> 00:53:14.700
Oh. man!

830
00:53:19.800 --> 00:53:21.700
Sid Phillips reporting.

831
00:53:21.800 --> 00:53:23.900
Launch of the shuttle
has been delayed...

832
00:53:23.900 --> 00:53:26.700
due to adverse weather
conditions at the launch site.

833
00:53:26.700 --> 00:53:29.800
Tomorrow's forecast: sunny.

834
00:53:29.700 --> 00:53:33.600
Sweet dreams.

835
00:53:37.500 --> 00:53:41.200
I looked everywhere. honey.
but all I could find was your hat.

836
00:53:41.100 --> 00:53:43.200
But what if we
leave them behind?

837
00:53:43.200 --> 00:53:48.200
Oh. don't worry. honey.
I'm sure we'll find Woody
and Buzz before we leave tomorrow.

838
00:53:55.300 --> 00:53:57.200
I need air!

839
00:53:57.300 --> 00:53:59.500
Why will you quit
movin' around?

840
00:53:59.500 --> 00:54:03.200
I'm sorry. It's just that I get-
I get so nervous before I travel.

841
00:54:03.100 --> 00:54:05.600
How did I get stuck
with you as a moving buddy?

842
00:54:05.600 --> 00:54:08.400
Everyone else was picked.

843
00:54:13.100 --> 00:54:15.000
Oh. Woody.

844
00:54:15.000 --> 00:54:20.100
If only you could see
how much Andy misses you.

845
00:54:31.800 --> 00:54:34.800
Psst. Psst! Hey. Buzz!

846
00:54:39.400 --> 00:54:41.800
Hey.

847
00:54:41.900 --> 00:54:47.000
Get over here and see if
you can get this toolbox off me.

848
00:54:46.800 --> 00:54:50.400
Oh. come on. Buzz. I--

849
00:54:50.400 --> 00:54:54.700
Buzz. I can't do this without you.
I need your help.

850
00:54:54.600 --> 00:54:58.900
I can't help.
I can't help anyone.

851
00:54:58.800 --> 00:55:02.100
Why. sure you can. Buzz.
You can get me outta here.

852
00:55:02.100 --> 00:55:05.000
Then I'll get that rocket off you.
and we'll make a break for Andy's house.

853
00:55:05.000 --> 00:55:08.200
Andy's house. Sid's house.
What's the difference?

854
00:55:08.200 --> 00:55:12.400
Oh. Buzz. You've had a big fall.
You must not be thinking clearly.

855
00:55:12.300 --> 00:55:15.600
No. Woody. For the first time
I am thinking clearly.

856
00:55:15.600 --> 00:55:19.200
You were right all along.
I'm not a Space Ranger.

857
00:55:19.200 --> 00:55:23.000
I'm just a toy. a stupid.
little. insignificant toy.

858
00:55:22.900 --> 00:55:24.800
Whoa. hey. wait a minute.

859
00:55:24.800 --> 00:55:27.500
Bein' a toy is a lot better
than bein' a. a Space Ranger.

860
00:55:27.500 --> 00:55:29.400
- Yeah. right.
- No. it is.

861
00:55:29.400 --> 00:55:32.300
Look. over in that house is a kid
who thinks you are the greatest.

862
00:55:32.300 --> 00:55:35.500
And it's not because
you're a Space Ranger. pal.

863
00:55:35.500 --> 00:55:39.300
It's because you're a toy.
You are his toy.

864
00:55:39.200 --> 00:55:41.300
But why would Andy want me?

865
00:55:41.300 --> 00:55:45.700
Why would Andy want you? Look at you!
You're a Buzz Lightyear.

866
00:55:45.600 --> 00:55:48.600
Any other toy would give up
his moving parts just to be you.

867
00:55:48.600 --> 00:55:52.300
You've got wings.
You glow in the dark. You talk!

868
00:55:52.200 --> 00:55:55.400
Your helmet does
that. that. that whoosh thing.

869
00:55:55.400 --> 00:55:59.800
You are a cool toy.

870
00:56:01.700 --> 00:56:05.100
As a matter of fact.
you're too cool.

871
00:56:05.100 --> 00:56:08.300
mean. I mean. what chance
does a toy like me have...

872
00:56:08.300 --> 00:56:11.600
against a Buzz Lightyear
action figure?

873
00:56:11.500 --> 00:56:14.100
All I can do is--

874
00:56:14.100 --> 00:56:18.500
There's a snake in my boots.

875
00:56:18.400 --> 00:56:20.400
Why would Andy ever want
to play with me...

876
00:56:20.400 --> 00:56:23.200
when he's got you?

877
00:56:23.200 --> 00:56:27.800
I'm the one that should be
strapped to that rocket.

878
00:56:49.300 --> 00:56:52.600
Listen. Buzz.
forget about me.

879
00:56:52.600 --> 00:56:55.500
You should get outta here
while you can.

880
00:57:05.500 --> 00:57:08.000
Buzz? What are you doin'?
I thought you were--

881
00:57:08.000 --> 00:57:11.000
Come on. Sheriff. There's a kid
over in that house who needs us.

882
00:57:11.000 --> 00:57:12.900
Now let's get you out of this thing.

883
00:57:12.900 --> 00:57:15.000
Yes. sir!

884
00:57:15.000 --> 00:57:18.800
- Come on. Buzz. We can do it.

885
00:57:24.200 --> 00:57:26.100
Woody. it's the moving van.

886
00:57:26.100 --> 00:57:28.800
We gotta get outta here now.

887
00:57:32.800 --> 00:57:35.300
Come on. Buzz.

888
00:57:36.400 --> 00:57:39.100
All right.
Buzz!

889
00:57:39.100 --> 00:57:41.800
- Hey. I'm out!
- Almost there.

890
00:57:45.400 --> 00:57:49.000
I want to ride the pony.

891
00:57:49.100 --> 00:57:53.200
Phew. Woody?

892
00:57:53.100 --> 00:57:56.600
Woody? Are you all right?

893
00:57:56.600 --> 00:57:59.100
I'm fine. I'm okay.

894
00:58:09.400 --> 00:58:13.500
Oh. yeah!
Time for liftoff! Whoo!

895
00:58:15.300 --> 00:58:17.900
To infinity and beyond!

896
00:58:26.600 --> 00:58:29.400
- Aah! Back. back.

897
00:58:29.400 --> 00:58:31.600
- Down. down!

898
00:58:31.600 --> 00:58:35.700
- Okay. what do I do?
Come on. Woody. Think.

899
00:58:36.800 --> 00:58:39.200
Guys!

900
00:58:39.200 --> 00:58:41.900
No. no. no. no! Wait!
Wait. Listen. please.

901
00:58:41.900 --> 00:58:45.900
There's a good toy down there. and he's
gonna be blown to bits in a few minutes.

902
00:58:45.800 --> 00:58:49.300
All because of me.
We've gotta save him.

903
00:58:49.300 --> 00:58:52.200
And. uh-
Bull need your help.

904
00:58:58.700 --> 00:59:03.200
Please. He's my friend.

905
00:59:03.100 --> 00:59:05.600
And he's the only one
I've got.

906
00:59:16.600 --> 00:59:21.200
Thank you.
Okay. I think I know what to do.

907
00:59:21.100 --> 00:59:23.600
We're gonna have
to break a few rules.

908
00:59:23.600 --> 00:59:26.700
But if it works.
it'll help everybody.

909
00:59:35.800 --> 00:59:39.800
- Houston to Mission Control.
Come in. Control.

910
00:59:39.700 --> 00:59:44.200
Launch pad is
being constructed.

911
00:59:44.100 --> 00:59:45.600
All right. listen up.

912
00:59:45.700 --> 00:59:48.500
need Pump Boy here.
Ducky here.

913
00:59:48.500 --> 00:59:52.300
- Legs. you're with Ducky.

914
00:59:52.200 --> 00:59:54.400
Roller Bob and I don't move
till we get the signal. Clear?

915
00:59:54.400 --> 00:59:57.900
- Okay. Let's move!

916
01:00:17.300 --> 01:00:19.200
Wind the frog.

917
01:00:40.200 --> 01:00:42.400
- Wait for the signal.

918
01:00:56.000 --> 01:00:58.600
- Go!

919
01:01:00.300 --> 01:01:03.800
- All right. let's go!

920
01:01:03.800 --> 01:01:05.700
I'll get it!

921
01:01:05.800 --> 01:01:08.100
Now!

922
01:01:08.100 --> 01:01:09.400
- I'm coming. I'm coming.

923
01:01:18.300 --> 01:01:20.200
- Scud!

924
01:01:23.700 --> 01:01:26.200
- Stupid dog.

925
01:01:31.700 --> 01:01:33.800
Lean back!

926
01:01:38.500 --> 01:01:43.500
Uh. Mission Control. is
the launch pad construction complete?

927
01:01:43.400 --> 01:01:46.000
Uh. roger. Rocket is now
secured to guide wire.

928
01:01:46.000 --> 01:01:49.200
We are currently obtaining
the ignition sticks.

929
01:01:49.200 --> 01:01:53.000
- Countdown will commence
momentarily. Standby.
- Let's go.

930
01:01:52.900 --> 01:01:57.300
Hey. Ma! Where are the matches?
Oh. wait. Here they are. Never mind

931
01:01:57.300 --> 01:01:59.800
- Woody! Great!
Help me outta this thing.
- Shh!

932
01:01:59.800 --> 01:02:02.200
- What?
- It's okay.

